        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratori</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Caes</abbr><ex>ari</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>ito</ex></expan><certainty match="preceding-sibling::node()" locus="value"/> <expan><abbr>Aelio</abbr><ex cert="low"/></expan> <lb n="2"/>Hadriano <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usto</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/>patri patriae <lb n="4"/>sublevatori orbis <lb n="5"/>restitutori ope<lb break="no" n="6"/>rum publicorum <lb n="7"/>indulgentissimo <lb n="8"/><expan><abbr>optimoq</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan> principi <lb n="9"/>Campani <lb n="10"/>ob insignem erga eos be<lb break="no" n="11"/>nignitatem <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecreto</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecurionum</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Nach Horster handelt es sich wahrscheinlich um eine Ehrung für Hadrian, bei der fälschlicherweise in Z. 1 T. Aelio statt Traiano abgeschrieben wurde.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography">
